{"id":"testimony","term":"Testimony","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(1.) Witness or evidence (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Thessalonians 1:10\">2 Thess. 1:10</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) The Scriptures, as the revelation of God’s will (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 11:12\">2 Kings 11:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 19:7\">Ps. 19:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 119:88\">119:88</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 8:16\">Isa. 8:16</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 8:20\">20</a>).</p>\n<p>(3.) The altar raised by the Gadites and Reubenites (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 22:10\">Josh. 22:10</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["2 Thessalonians 1:10","2 Kings 11:12","Psalms 19:7","Psalms 119:88","Isaiah 8:16","Isaiah 8:20","Joshua 22:10"]}